            <title>[CASSANDRA-16707] JmxHistogram#getRecentValues() is not thread-safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16707</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Published &lt;tt&gt;JmxHistogram&lt;/tt&gt; instances do not protect their &#8220;last&#8221; field. This isn&#8217;t a hot path, and there is a multi-part calculation based on it in &lt;tt&gt;getRecentValues()&lt;/tt&gt;, so we should probably just synchronize that method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
